# Workspace Directory Structure

This file documents the directory structure that /knz-init creates when scaffolding
a new curriculum project. It is a reference for the init command — not actual
directories in the template.

## Directories Created by /knz-init

```
workspace/{project-name}/
  01-project-brief/
  02-outcomes/
  03-assessments/
  04-modules/
  05-sessions/
  06-metaskills/
  07-transfer/
  08-marketing/
  09-validation/
  delivery/
```

## Directory Purpose

| Directory         | Pipeline Stage | Content                                          |
|-------------------|---------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| 01-project-brief/ | Stage 1       | Intake brief and key decision record             |
| 02-outcomes/      | Stage 2       | Learning outcomes (competency + performance)     |
| 03-assessments/   | Stage 3       | Assessment designs aligned to outcomes           |
| 04-modules/       | Stage 4       | Module-level structure and learning arcs         |
| 05-sessions/      | Stage 5       | Session-level content with TMA arc               |
| 06-metaskills/    | Stage 6       | Metaskill mapping per module                     |
| 07-transfer/      | Stage 7       | Transfer ecosystem (pre/in/post-program)         |
| 08-marketing/     | Stage 8       | Marketing copy derived from outcomes             |
| 09-validation/    | Stage 9       | Validation report and gap analysis               |
| delivery/         | Output        | Formatted HTML output (markdown is source truth) |

## Notes

- New projects use 01-09 directory numbering matching stage numbers 1-9
- Existing projects may use legacy 00-08 numbering — all commands auto-detect which scheme is present
- Stage-numbered directories match the `output_dir` from each pipeline schema
- `delivery/` is for formatted HTML output — markdown in stage dirs is source of truth
- No placeholder files or template stubs in any directory
- Each pipeline command creates its output files when it runs
- /knz-init creates STATE.md and CLAUDE.md alongside these directories
